{'title': 'WiFi Automatic', 'description': 'This simple app can help you increase the standby time of your device: <b>WiFi Automatic</b> automatically disable your WiFi radio when you don\'t need it and thereby lowers the battery consumption.\r\n\r\nYou can also specify to automatically turn on WiFi again, if you turn on your device or when you enter a specified location (requires a cell radio and therefore does not work on WiFi-only tablets!). Also, the app can regularly scan for available networks to connect to and re-disable WiFi if no suitable network is found. This way, you are always connected to your WiFi network when using the device.\r\n\r\n<i>WiFi Automatic</i> is open source: https://github.com/j4velin/WiFi-Automatic\r\n\r\nA WiFi connection generally uses less power than a mobile data connection, so on your phone, it makes sense to keep the WiFi radio active, whenever a WiFi network is in range\r\n\r\n\r\n--------------------\r\nPermissions: \r\nRECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED - is required to start the service again when rebooting your device\r\n\r\nThe following permissions are required to observe and change the WiFi state:\r\nCHANGE_WIFI_STATE\r\nACCESS_NETWORK_STATE\r\nACCESS_WIFI_STATE\r\n\r\nThe following permissions are required to the "turn on WiFi when entering these locations" feature:\r\nINTERNET\r\nWRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE\r\nACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION\r\nACCESS_FINE_LOCATION\r\nBILLING', 'descriptionHTML': 'This simple app can help you increase the standby time of your device: <b>WiFi Automatic</b> automatically disable your WiFi radio when you don&#39;t need it and thereby lowers the battery consumption.<br><br>You can also specify to automatically turn on WiFi again, if you turn on your device or when you enter a specified location (requires a cell radio and therefore does not work on WiFi-only tablets!). Also, the app can regularly scan for available networks to connect to and re-disable WiFi if no suitable network is found. This way, you are always connected to your WiFi network when using the device.<br><br><i>WiFi Automatic</i> is open source: https://github.com/j4velin/WiFi-Automatic<br><br>A WiFi connection generally uses less power than a mobile data connection, so on your phone, it makes sense to keep the WiFi radio active, whenever a WiFi network is in range<br><br><br>--------------------<br>Permissions: <br>RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED - is required to start the service again when rebooting your device<br><br>The following permissions are required to observe and change the WiFi state:<br>CHANGE_WIFI_STATE<br>ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE<br>ACCESS_WIFI_STATE<br><br>The following permissions are required to the &quot;turn on WiFi when entering these locations&quot; feature:<br>INTERNET<br>WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE<br>ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION<br>ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION<br>BILLING', 'summary': 'Automatically turn WiFi on and off to save battery', 'summaryHTML': 'Automatically turn WiFi on and off to save battery', 'installs': '1,000,000+', 'minInstalls': 1000000, 'score': 4.232984, 'ratings': 15960, 'reviews': 4980, 'histogram': [1702, 543, 1148, 1504, 11061], 'price': 0, 'free': True, 'currency': 'USD', 'sale': False, 'saleTime': None, 'originalPrice': None, 'saleText': None, 'offersIAP': True, 'size': 'Varies with device', 'androidVersion': 'Varies', 'androidVersionText': 'Varies with device', 'developer': 'j4velin', 'developerId': '6602470455848506235', 'developerEmail': 'j4velin.development+play@gmail.com', 'developerWebsite': 'http://www.j4velin.de', 'developerAddress': 'Thomas Hoffmann\nSchwanhäußerstr. 5\n90408 Nürnberg', 'privacyPolicy': 'https://j4velin.de/?action=privacy', 'developerInternalID': '6602470455848506235', 'genre': 'Tools', 'genreId': 'TOOLS', 'icon': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/DPdO0Zc2ixNIRrO6abSoc1TE7mu7NUjNdsSWCgecrN2iJs4ylYZ4cFO52T5RBzOLg30', 'headerImage': 'https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/5XqScOU-xDVrFji491AIl2kAHXAqwFJNrgnzlQdElVtd09lzshIBl5hWycH3dWTUnA', 'screenshots': ['https://lh3.googleus